questionTemplates.text:
M: I am taking this great course-Psychology of Language, it's really interesting. Since you are a psychology major, you should sign up for it.
W: Actually I tried to do that, but they told me I have to take language studies first.
{a}

M: Frankly, when I sat the back of the classroom, I can't see the words on the board clearly.
W: Well, you've been wearing those same glasses as long as I've known you. Why not get a new pair? It wouldn't cost you too much.
{a}

M: The students will get to the museum at 9:30, won't they?
W: Yes. They will leave at 11 o'clock.
{a}

M: Did you find a purse you like?
W: Yes. I got a lovely one for $30 at Hayward's, but I saw today that they're on sale for $20. I would have saved $10 if I had only known.
{a}

F: Nice to meet you. I work in a travel agency. How about you?
M: Well, I'm working in a bank.
{a}

M: I'd like to ask you about the research paper you assigned that we have to do by the end of the semester.
W: OK. What would you like to know?
{a}

M: My parents like Beijing very much, because they were born there.
F: Oh, really? So Beijing is their hometown.
{a}

M: I'm 60 years old. Is it possible for me to learn drawing?
W: It's never too old to learn.
{a}

W: Would you like a cup of tea?
M: Thank you, but I prefer coffee to tea.
{a}

M: Look, he has kicked a goal again.
W: Yes. It was a wonderful kick.
{a}

W: It's such a nice day. Why don't we have lunch outside?
M: OK. But let's find some place that's not too noisy.
{a}

W: Oh! It's 7:00 now!
M: Hurry up. The bus leaves in ten minutes.
{a}

M: Please excuse me for coming late.
W: It's not your fault. After all, it's the busiest time of the day.
{a}

M: I can't find my pen anywhere. It was on the desk with my book a moment ago.
W: Look! Here it is. You left it by the phone.
{a}

W: Why are you so late? We've been waiting almost an hour and a half.
M: I'm terribly sorry. Just as I was leaving, Mr Smith asked me to send a telegram for him. The post office was crowded and I was in line for an hour. Then I raced straight here.
{a}

Man: I've got my camera with me. Am I allowed to take photos here?
Woman: I think so. It doesn't say you can't.
{a}

W: Hey, if you can't enjoy the music at a sensible volume, why not use earphones?I'm preparing for the speech contest.
M: Oh, sorry. I didn't realize I've being bothering you all this time.
{a}

W: Well, Tonight we have Prof. Brown in the studio to talk about his recent book, Fashion Images. Good evening.
M: Good evening, and thank you for inviting me here this evening.
{a}

M: Are you going to tell Ms. Martin that you are looking for another job?
W: No, not yet. Besides, if I don't find one, I'll stay here a while longer.
{a}

M: The students English Club is having a party on Saturday night. Can you come?
W: I would like to but I work at a restaurant on weekend.
{a}

M: Jessica, could you this emails to all the club members?
W: Sorry, the computer broke down this morning. I will for you as soon as I have fixed.
{a}

W: Would you like to see the menu?
M: No, thank you. I know what to order.
{a}

W: Don't you want to buy the sunglasses? They suit your face shape.
M: Well. I would have bought them right away if they were brown. I don't like black ones.
{a}
